---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
  { name: 'For Breed Clubs', url: '/for-breed-clubs' }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What does it cost for a breed club to partner with BreederHQ?',
    answer: 'Nothing, during founding partner program. Your club and your members aren\'t charged for the club tooling, we\'re investing in this as a flagship feature. In exchange, we ask you to help us shape the admin tools and give us honest feedback about what your club actually needs. Long-term pricing will be transparent and proportionate to club size; we\'ll never charge per-animal or take a cut of registrations.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Do my members have to switch from another tool?',
    answer: 'No. Most of our breeder members are already tracking animals, health tests, and pedigrees on BreederHQ because it\'s the best-in-class tool for running their breeding program day-to-day. Your club registration becomes one more piece of structured data alongside everything they already have, not a new system they have to learn.'
  },
  {
    question: 'We already have a stud book on [WordPress / Excel / old database]. How does that migrate?',
    answer: 'We\'ll help you import it. During onboarding we sit down with you, map your fields to ours, and move the historical stud book over. Registrations going forward flow in naturally as your members record animals.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Who owns the data?',
    answer: 'Your club owns your registrations. Your members own their animal data. BreederHQ hosts and organizes it but never sells or licenses it. You can export your full stud book as CSV or JSON at any time. If you ever leave the platform, you walk away with everything.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What about privacy? Our members are protective of their bloodlines.',
    answer: 'Privacy is opt-in at every level. A member\'s club registration is private by default, visible to them and to your club, but not to the public marketplace or to other breeders searching the network. Members decide per-registration whether to opt into network visibility. Your members stay in control of their data.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can we require specific health tests as a condition of registration?',
    answer: 'Yes. You configure the registration requirements, full, limited, foundation types, required health clearances, pedigree proof, age requirements, fee structure. Applications that don\'t meet them flag automatically. Your reviewers see everything needed to approve or reject without chasing members for attachments.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What if two members both claim the same animal or the same stud?',
    answer: 'BreederHQ animals are identifiable across the entire platform. A stud owned by Member A can be linked as the sire of Member B\'s litter only with Member A\'s approval. The data makes cross-member disputes solvable, you can see the full provenance chain, not take one side\'s word against the other.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Is the club admin portal live today?',
    answer: 'The breeder-facing side is live: members are recording club registrations, health tests, pedigrees, and opting into network-visible stud book browsing right now, today. The dedicated admin dashboard, approval queue view, aggregated member directory, club-wide stud book browser, admin login, is the Phase 3 work we\'re building with founding partners. Being a founding partner means you help us decide what gets built first and how it works.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can our members get a discount on their BreederHQ subscription?',
    answer: 'Yes. Partnering clubs get member-discount pricing set up during onboarding. The most common structure is a percentage off the standard subscription tier for verified dues-paid members, with a co-branded signup flow that activates the discount automatically when a member joins your club. We also offer bundled bulk licensing (the club pays a flat rate, your members get seats at no individual cost) and optional revenue share arrangements. We configure the structure that makes sense for your club size and member base.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What about discounts on marketplace listing fees?',
    answer: 'Same answer: partner clubs can unlock reduced or waived marketplace listing fees for member-owned animals. Your members get more economical listings, you get a tangible benefit that strengthens your membership value proposition, and you can advertise that benefit on your own recruitment materials.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How do we apply?',
    answer: 'Reach out below. We\'ll schedule a 30-minute call to understand your club\'s current workflow, show you what\'s live today, walk through what we\'re building, and, if it\'s a fit, start onboarding. No pressure, no contract required up front.'
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="For Breed Clubs | BreederHQ"
  description="The home of the breed. BreederHQ gives your breed club a live stud book, structured health and pedigree data, an approval workflow for registrations, and a direct connection to the breeders who already work on the platform every day. Founding partner program open."
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  faqs={faqs}
>

  <main>

    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- HERO                                         -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-amber-50 via-orange-50 to-white py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="text-center">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-amber-100 border border-amber-300 text-amber-900 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-6">
            <span aria-hidden>🏛</span>
            <span>Founding Partner Program</span>
          </div>
          <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-6xl leading-tight mb-6">
            Your Breed Club.<br />
            <span class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)]">Finally on Modern Tools.</span>
          </h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            A breed club runs on volunteer labor and a patchwork of 20-year-old software.
            Your stud book is a PDF. Your dues are a spreadsheet. Your event registration
            is a Google Form. Your member directory is out of date the day you publish it.
          </p>
          <p class="text-xl text-gray-900 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-10 leading-relaxed font-semibold">
            BreederHQ is your club's operational home, the stud book, the member directory,
            the event management, the health surveillance, the communications, all in one
            place, powered by the data your members are already entering every day.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
            <a
              href="/contact?topic=breed-club-partnership"
              class="bg-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg text-lg font-semibold hover:bg-[hsl(24,95%,45%)] w-full sm:w-auto"
            >
              Talk to Us About Partnering
            </a>
            <a
              href="#what-your-club-gets"
              class="text-gray-600 px-8 py-4 text-lg font-medium hover:text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] w-full sm:w-auto"
            >
              See What's Already Live &rarr;
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- THE PROBLEM TODAY                            -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-stone-50">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
            Running a Breed Club in 2026 Is Harder Than It Should Be
          </h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            Your members are dedicated. Your standards are real. But the tools you have to
            do this work? They haven't changed in 20 years.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-stone-200">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-2xl shrink-0">📄</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Your stud book is a PDF</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                  Published twice a year, six months out of date the day it drops, and
                  impossible for anyone, including you, to actually search.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-stone-200">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-2xl shrink-0">📮</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Applications arrive by paper, check, or email</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                  A form here, a PDF health report there, a pedigree scan, and you
                  re-key all of it into a spreadsheet. One litter takes an hour of
                  someone's volunteer time.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-stone-200">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-2xl shrink-0">💸</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Dues tracking is somebody's side job</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                  A PayPal inbox, a Google Sheet, a separate membership tier spreadsheet,
                  and an annual email asking "did you pay? I can't find the receipt." Renewal
                  reminders are manual. Lapsed members just vanish without anyone noticing.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-stone-200">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-2xl shrink-0">📅</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Every event is a fresh improvisation</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                  National Specialty entries go through one system. Regional seminars use
                  a different one. Fun matches use a Google Form. The catalog is hand-typed
                  from email responses. Show results are PDFs nobody can search.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-stone-200">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-2xl shrink-0">🧬</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Health data doesn't flow back to you</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                  Your members test. You require it. But the results live in a
                  member's filing cabinet, you can't see breed-wide trends or spot
                  outliers, only what gets manually submitted. Health surveys get 10%
                  response rates.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-stone-200">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-2xl shrink-0">✉️</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Communicating with members is a mailing list from 2008</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                  Yahoo Groups closed, the replacement is clunky, members miss half the
                  emails, and nobody knows who's actually a current member vs. lurker.
                  Announcements go into a void; responses come back scattered across
                  four different channels.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-stone-200">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-2xl shrink-0">🔀</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Members live in five different systems</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                  BreederHQ for management. AKC online for papers. Email for registrations.
                  Facebook Groups for community. Spreadsheets for everything else. No
                  single source of truth, and you're the last one to know when something changes.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-stone-200">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-2xl shrink-0">🔍</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Your breeder referral list is a PDF</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                  Someone asks "do you know of a breeder in Ohio with a litter this spring?"
                  and the answer is either "check our website PDF" (last updated in January)
                  or "email the secretary." That's the public face of your breed.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-stone-200">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-2xl shrink-0">🕵️</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">You can't tell who's actively breeding</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                  Your member list is dues-paid vs. lapsed. You have no idea which members
                  are on their 8th litter this year and which haven't bred in a decade.
                  That affects everything from mentorship matching to succession planning.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-stone-200">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <span class="text-2xl shrink-0">⚖️</span>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Disputes come down to "whose word do we trust?"</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
                  When two members claim the same stud, or a litter's sire is disputed,
                  or a health clearance's validity is questioned, or a Code of Ethics
                  complaint comes in, you have paperwork and testimony. No data.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-10 text-center">
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 font-medium max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            Your members deserve better. Your breed deserves better.
            <br />And you deserve to get your Saturdays back.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- WHAT YOUR CLUB GETS                          -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-white" id="what-your-club-gets">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="text-center mb-14">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
            What Your Club Gets on BreederHQ
          </h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            Every capability below is powered by the data and infrastructure already
            running on BreederHQ for your members. Your club doesn't build any of it.
            It just shows up, ready to use.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Legend for maturity labels -->
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-4 mb-10 text-xs">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-green-50 border border-green-200 text-green-800">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-green-500"></span>
            <span class="font-semibold">Live today</span>
          </div>
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 text-amber-800">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-amber-500"></span>
            <span class="font-semibold">Phase 3, built with founding partners</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

          <!-- Live Stud Book -->
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-orange-50 rounded-xl p-8 border border-amber-200">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-amber-200 flex items-center justify-center text-2xl shrink-0">📖</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">A live, queryable stud book</h3>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
                  <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-green-500"></span>
                  <span class="text-xs text-green-800 font-medium">Breeder side live</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-400 mx-1">•</span>
                  <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-amber-500"></span>
                  <span class="text-xs text-amber-800 font-medium">Admin view Phase 3</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-amber-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Every animal registered with your club, across every member, in one view
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-amber-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Searchable by bloodline, sex, age, health status, registration type
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-amber-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Updated in real time, the moment a member enters a record, you see it
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-amber-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Export the full stud book as CSV, PDF, or via API. It's your data.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <!-- Structured Data -->
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 rounded-xl p-8 border border-blue-200">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-blue-200 flex items-center justify-center text-2xl shrink-0">🧬</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Structured data, not PDF attachments</h3>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
                  <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-green-500"></span>
                  <span class="text-xs text-green-800 font-medium">Live today</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-blue-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Health tests: OFA hips, elbows, DNA clearances, as structured records, not PDFs
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-blue-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Pedigrees: linked animals, not typed text. Verified against the real stud.
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-blue-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Genetics: coat color, health markers, breed-specific loci, all queryable
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-blue-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Titles and show records, linked to the organization that awarded them
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <!-- Approval Workflow -->
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 rounded-xl p-8 border border-green-200">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-green-200 flex items-center justify-center text-2xl shrink-0">✅</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Registration approval workflow</h3>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
                  <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-green-500"></span>
                  <span class="text-xs text-green-800 font-medium">Data layer live</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-400 mx-1">•</span>
                  <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-amber-500"></span>
                  <span class="text-xs text-amber-800 font-medium">Admin queue Phase 3</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                You define registration types: Full, Limited, Foundation, Conditional
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                You set health testing requirements per registration type
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Members submit applications with supporting data pre-attached
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Pending queue with health compliance status flagged automatically
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Approve, reject, or send back with notes, resubmission keeps history
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <!-- Member Roster & Directory -->
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-violet-50 to-purple-50 rounded-xl p-8 border border-violet-200">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-violet-200 flex items-center justify-center text-2xl shrink-0">👥</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Member roster and directory</h3>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
                  <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-green-500"></span>
                  <span class="text-xs text-green-800 font-medium">Directory live</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-400 mx-1">•</span>
                  <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-amber-500"></span>
                  <span class="text-xs text-amber-800 font-medium">Club-facing admin Phase 3</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-violet-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Live member roster: contact info, membership tier, join date, renewal date, dues status
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-violet-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Multiple tiers configurable: Full, Associate, Junior, Life, Honorary, Lifetime, whatever you have. Different dues, different permissions.
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-violet-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Segment members by tier, region, activity level, breeding frequency, compliance status
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-violet-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                See who's active vs. lapsed vs. dues-paid-but-silent. Target outreach accordingly.
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-violet-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Self-service profile updates: members keep their own contact info current. No more "return to sender" mailings.
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-violet-600 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                CSV export for your treasurer or historical records
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <!-- Dues, Fees & Renewals via Stripe -->
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-fuchsia-50 to-purple-50 rounded-xl p-8 border border-fuchsia-300">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-4">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-fuchsia-200 flex items-center justify-center text-2xl shrink-0">💳</div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Dues, fees, and renewals (Stripe-powered)</h3>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
                  <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-green-500"></span>
                  <span class="text-xs text-green-800 font-medium">Stripe infrastructure live</span>
                  <span class="text-gray-400 mx-1">•</span>
                  <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-amber-500"></span>
                  <span class="text-xs text-amber-800 font-medium">Club configuration UI Phase 3</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-3">
              We already run Stripe Connect for platform subscriptions, marketplace
              listing fees, breeding program offspring fees, and service provider
              billing. Your club's dues collection plugs into that same pipeline with
              your club as the merchant of record.
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-fuchsia-700 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Automated annual dues billing with recurring Stripe subscriptions per member
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-fuchsia-700 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Renewal reminders 90, 60, 30 days out via email. Auto-pay for members who opt in.
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-fuchsia-700 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Failed-payment dunning: Stripe automatically retries, notifies the member, escalates to you if unresolved
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-fuchsia-700 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                Grace periods, pro-rated joins, comped honorary members, lifetime members. You set the rules.
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-fuchsia-700 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
                One-time fees alongside recurring: registration fees, event entries, merchandise, donations, all through the same payment rails
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-fuchsia-700 mt-0.5 font-bold">&#10003;</span>
